itemDescription: Baron in the Peerage of the United Kingdom (1860-1940)

wikipedia_page.main: Samuel James Waring, 1st Baron Waring (19 April 1860 – 9 January 1940), known as Sir Samuel Waring, Bt, between 1919 and 1922, was a British industrialist, public servant and benefactor.

response: The Waring Baronetcy, of Foots Cray Place in the County of Kent, was created in the Baronetage of the United Kingdom on 31 May 1919. For more information on this creation, see Samuel Waring, 1st Baron Waring.
